{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877748409,"sessionID":"ses_2857033aaffejPGU5jmg3VBHyU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8fedb20010w8S0njtZsWNN7","messageID":"msg_d7a8fe1140011S2K6Cfrhg4xrM","sessionID":"ses_2857033aaffejPGU5jmg3VBHyU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_6c34cd44bdd94b4daa8b2409","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-035/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-035/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-035 вҖ” client-go зұ»еһӢе®ўжҲ·з«Ҝз”ҹжҲҗ\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: з”ҹжҲҗ Kubernetes client д»Јз ҒпјҢз”ЁдәҺ API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh / v1alpha1`пјҢжЁЎеқ—и·Ҝеҫ„ `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`гҖӮиҜҘе®ўжҲ·з«Ҝеә“йҒөеҫӘ Kubernetes client-go и§„иҢғпјҢжҸҗдҫӣ typed clientгҖҒinformerгҖҒlister е®Ңж•ҙз”ҹжҖҒгҖӮ\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Architecture\n10: \n11: ### Directory Structure\n12: \n13: ```\n14: client-go/\n15: в”ңв”Җв”Җ clientset/\n16: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ versioned/\n17: в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ clientset.go              # Clientset дё»е…ҘеҸЈ\n18: в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ scheme/                   # зұ»еһӢжіЁеҶҢ\n19: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ register.go\n20: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ doc.go\n21: в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ typed/\n22: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ runtime/\n23: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ v1alpha1/\n24: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ           в”ңв”Җв”Җ runtime_client.go\n25: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ           в”ңв”Җв”Җ agentruntime.go\n26: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ           в”ңв”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter.go\n27: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ           в”ңв”Җв”Җ generated_expansion.go\n28: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ           в”ңв”Җв”Җ doc.go\n29: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ           в””в”Җв”Җ fake/\n30: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ               в”ңв”Җв”Җ fake_runtime_client.go\n31: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ               в”ңв”Җв”Җ fake_agentruntime.go\n32: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ               в”ңв”Җв”Җ fake_codeinterpreter.go\n33: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ               в””в”Җв”Җ doc.go\n34: в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ fake/\n35: в”Ӯ           в”ңв”Җв”Җ clientset_generated.go\n36: в”Ӯ           в”ңв”Җв”Җ register.go\n37: в”Ӯ           в””в”Җв”Җ doc.go\n38: в”ңв”Җв”Җ informers/\n39: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ externalversions/\n40: в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ factory.go                 # SharedInformerFactory\n41: в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ generic.go                 # GenericInformer и·Ҝз”ұ\n42: в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ runtime/\n43: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ interface.go           # Group жҺҘеҸЈ\n44: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ v1alpha1/\n45: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ interface.go       # Version жҺҘеҸЈ\n46: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ agentruntime.go\n47: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter.go\n48: в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ internalinterfaces/\n49: в”Ӯ           в””в”Җв”Җ factory_interfaces.go\n50: в””в”Җв”Җ listers/\n51:     в””в”Җв”Җ runtime/\n52:         в””в”Җв”Җ v1alpha1/\n53:             в”ңв”Җв”Җ agentruntime.go\n54:             в”ңв”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter.go\n55:             в””в”Җв”Җ expansion_generated.go\n56: ```\n57: \n58: ### Component Responsibilities\n59: \n60: | Component | Responsibility |\n61: |-----------|----------------|\n62: | Clientset | йЎ¶еұӮе…ҘеҸЈпјҢз®ЎзҗҶжүҖжңү group зүҲжң¬е®ўжҲ·з«ҜпјҢж”ҜжҢҒ Discovery е’Ң RuntimeV1alpha1 |\n63: | Typed Client | REST е°ҒиЈ…пјҢжҸҗдҫӣ CRUD + Watch + Patch ж“ҚдҪң |\n64: | Informer | зј“еӯҳ + жҺ§еҲ¶еҷЁжЁЎејҸпјҢиҮӘеҠЁеҗҢжӯҘ Kubernetes иө„жәҗ |\n65: | Lister | еҸӘиҜ»зј“еӯҳжҹҘиҜўпјҢж”ҜжҢҒ namespace зә§еҲ«иҝҮж»Ө |\n66: | Scheme | зұ»еһӢеәҸеҲ—еҢ–е’ҢеҸҚеәҸеҲ—еҢ–жіЁеҶҢ |\n67: | Fake Client | жөӢиҜ•з”ЁеҶ…еӯҳе®һзҺ° |\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## API Design\n72: \n73: ### Clientset Interface\n74: \n75: ```go\n76: type Interface interface {\n77:     Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n78:     RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n79: }\n80: ```\n81: \n82: **Constructors:**\n83: - `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n84: - `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n85: - `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n86: - `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n87: \n88: ### Typed Client: RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n92:     RESTClient() rest.Interface\n93:     AgentRuntimesGetter\n94:     CodeInterpretersGetter\n95: }\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### AgentRuntimeInterface\n99: \n100: ```go\n101: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n102:     Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n103:     Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n104:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n105:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n106:     DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n107:     Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n108:     List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n109:     Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n110:     Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n111:     AgentRuntimeExpansion\n112: }\n113: ```\n114: \n115: REST Resource: `agentruntimes`\n116: \n117: ### CodeInterpreterInterface\n118: \n119: дёҺ AgentRuntimeInterface зӣёеҗҢз»“жһ„пјҢзұ»еһӢдёә `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`пјҢREST Resource: `codeinterpreters`\n120: \n121: ### Informer Factory\n122: \n123: ```go\n124: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n125:     internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n126:     Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n127:     Shutdown()\n128:     WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n129:     ForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n130:     InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n131:     Runtime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n132: }\n133: ```\n134: \n135: **Options:**\n136: - `NewSharedInformerFactory(client, defaultResync time.Duration)`\n137: - `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options ...SharedInformerOption)`\n138: - Options: `WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n139: \n140: ### Lister\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n144:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n145:     AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n146:     AgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n147: }\n148: \n149: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n150:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n151:     Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n152:     AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n153: }\n154: ```\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ## Code Generation\n159: \n160: ### Generation Tool\n161: \n162: дҪҝз”Ё `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1\n163: \n164: ### Generation Commands\n165: \n166: ```bash\n167: make gen-client\n168: # жҲ–\n169: hack/update-codegen.sh\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ### Generation Flags\n173: \n174: - `--with-watch`: ж”ҜжҢҒ Watch жңәеҲ¶\n175: - Output package: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n176: \n177: ### Source Reference\n178: \n179: API зұ»еһӢе®ҡд№үжәҗ: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/` (еҢ…еҗ« runtime/v1alpha1 зұ»еһӢе®ҡд№ү)\n180: \n181: ---\n182: \n183: ## Error Handling\n184: \n185: ### Client Errors\n186: \n187: - REST и°ғз”Ёиҝ”еӣһ `*meta.StatusError` ж—¶и§Јжһҗдёә `errors.NewStatusError`\n188: - зҪ‘з»ңй”ҷиҜҜгҖҒи¶…ж—¶зӣҙжҺҘдј йҖ’ Go error\n189: \n190: ### Informer Errors\n191: \n192: - `WaitForCacheSync` иҝ”еӣһеҗ„ resource зҡ„еҗҢжӯҘзҠ¶жҖҒ\n193: - еҗҢжӯҘеӨұиҙҘдёҚеҪұе“Қе…¶д»–иө„жәҗпјҢз»§з»ӯйҮҚиҜ•\n194: \n195: ### Retry Strategy\n196: \n197: - дҪҝз”Ё client-go еҶ…зҪ® retry жңәеҲ¶ (й»ҳи®ӨжҢҮж•°йҖҖйҒҝ)\n198: - еҸҜйҖҡиҝҮ `NewForConfigAndClient` жіЁе…ҘиҮӘе®ҡд№ү RoundTripper\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ## Testing Strategy\n203: \n204: ### Unit Tests\n205: \n206: - **Fake Client**: дҪҝз”Ё `clientset/versioned/fake/` дёӯзҡ„ fake е®һзҺ°\n207:   - `NewSimpleClientset()` вҖ” ж—  watch зј“еӯҳзҡ„з®ҖеҚ•е®һзҺ°\n208:   - `NewClientset()` вҖ” е®Ңж•ҙе®һзҺ°\n209: \n210: - **Lister Tests**: жөӢиҜ•зј“еӯҳжҹҘиҜўгҖҒnamespace иҝҮж»ӨгҖҒselector еҢ№й…Қ\n211: \n212: - **Informer Tests**: жөӢиҜ•дәӢд»¶еӨ„зҗҶгҖҒзј“еӯҳеҗҢжӯҘ\n213: \n214: ### Integration Tests\n215: \n216: - еҗҜеҠЁжң¬ең° Kubernetes (kind/minikube)\n217: - жөӢиҜ• CRUD ж“ҚдҪңдёҺзңҹе®һ API server дәӨдә’\n218: \n219: ### Fake Client Usage Example\n220: \n221: ```go\n222: import (\n223:     \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n224:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/fake\"\n225: )\n226: \n227: clientset := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n228: ```\n229: \n230: ---\n231: \n232: ## Security Considerations\n233: \n234: ### Authentication\n235: \n236: - ж”ҜжҢҒ kubeconfig дёӯзҡ„жүҖжңүи®ӨиҜҒж–№ејҸ (Bearer TokenгҖҒCertificateгҖҒOIDC)\n237: - йҖҡиҝҮ `rest.Config` жіЁе…ҘиҮӘе®ҡд№үеҮӯиҜҒ\n238: \n239: ### Authorization\n240: \n241: - йҒөеҫӘ Kubernetes RBACпјҢclient з«ҜдёҚеҒҡйўқеӨ–жҺҲжқғжЈҖжҹҘ\n242: \n243: ### Rate Limiting\n244: \n245: - еҸҜйҖҡиҝҮиҮӘе®ҡд№ү `http.Client` жіЁе…ҘйҷҗжөҒдёӯй—ҙд»¶\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ## Performance Optimization\n250: \n251: ### Informer Cache\n252: \n253: - й»ҳи®Ө in-memory зј“еӯҳпјҢж”ҜжҢҒ CustomResyncConfig и°ғдјҳ\n254: - дҪҝз”Ё `WithNamespace` йҷҗеҲ¶зј“еӯҳиҢғеӣҙ\n255: \n256: ### Lister Index\n257: \n258: - дҪҝз”Ё `cache.Indexer` ж”ҜжҢҒиҮӘе®ҡд№үзҙўеј•\n259: - й»ҳи®ӨжҢү namespace зҙўеј•\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ## Dependencies\n264: \n265: | Package | Version |\n266: |---------|---------|\n267: | k8s.io/client-go | v0.34.1 |\n268: | k8s.io/api | v0.34.1 |\n269: | k8s.io/apimachinery | v0.34.1 |\n270: | k8s.io/code-generator | v0.34.1 |\n271: \n272: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 272 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-035 вҖ” client-go зұ»еһӢе®ўжҲ·з«Ҝз”ҹжҲҗ\n\n## Overview\n\nз”ҹжҲҗ Kubernetes client д»Јз ҒпјҢз”ЁдәҺ API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh / v1alpha1`пјҢжЁЎеқ—и·Ҝеҫ„ `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`гҖӮиҜҘе®ўжҲ·з«Ҝеә“йҒөеҫӘ Kubernetes client-go и§„иҢғпјҢжҸҗдҫӣ typed clientгҖҒinformerгҖҒlister е®Ңж•ҙз”ҹжҖҒгҖӮ\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\nclient-go/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ clientset/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ versioned/\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ clientset.go              # Clientset дё»е…ҘеҸЈ\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ scheme/                   # зұ»еһӢжіЁеҶҢ\nв”Ӯ       в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ register.go\nв”Ӯ       в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ doc.go","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-035/design.md","time":{"start":1775877748389,"end":1775877748408}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877748412,"sessionID":"ses_2857033aaffejPGU5jmg3VBHyU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8ff222001a6797F1S4LHLCL","messageID":"msg_d7a8fe1140011S2K6Cfrhg4xrM","sessionID":"ses_2857033aaffejPGU5jmg3VBHyU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_77ead617fa334e78b2216a29","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-035 вҖ” client-go зұ»еһӢе®ўжҲ·з«Ҝз”ҹжҲҗ\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for generating the Kubernetes client-go library for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-035\n10: - **Module**: client-go\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: L\n13: - **Base Spec**: `deployment/client-go.md`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenario: Clientset Generation\n18: \n19: ### AR-035-001: Clientset Interface\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** a Go package at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned`\n22: - **WHEN** running code-generator with output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n23: - **THEN** there SHALL be an `Interface` with `Discovery()` and `RuntimeV1alpha1()` methods\n24: \n25: ### AR-035-002: Clientset struct\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** the clientset implementation\n28: - **WHEN** defining the Clientset struct\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`\n30: \n31: ### AR-035-003: Clientset constructors\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** the Clientset struct\n34: - **WHEN** creating constructors\n35: - **THEN** there SHALL be `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n36: - **AND** SHALL be `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n37: - **AND** SHALL be `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n38: - **AND** SHALL be `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## Scenario: Typed Client Generation\n43: \n44: ### AR-035-004: RuntimeV1alpha1Client Interface\n45: \n46: - **GIVEN** the typed client package at `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1`\n47: - **WHEN** generating the typed client\n48: - **THEN** there SHALL be `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` with `RESTClient() rest.Interface` and `AgentRuntimesGetter` / `CodeInterpretersGetter`\n49: \n50: ### AR-035-005: RuntimeV1alpha1Client struct\n51: \n52: - **GIVEN** RuntimeV1alpha1Client implementation\n53: - **WHEN** defining the client struct\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL implement `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n55: - **AND** SHALL have REST defaults: `GroupVersion` = `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.SchemeGroupVersion, `APIPath` = `/apis`\n56: \n57: ### AR-035-006: AgentRuntime typed client\n58: \n59: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime typed client\n60: - **WHEN** defining AgentRuntimeInterface\n61: - **THEN** it SHALL include Create, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete, DeleteCollection, Get, List, Watch, Patch methods\n62: - **AND** SHALL embed `AgentRuntimeExpansion`\n63: \n64: ### AR-035-007: AgentRuntime REST resource\n65: \n66: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeInterface\n67: - **WHEN** defining REST resource\n68: - **THEN** the resource plural SHALL be `agentruntimes`\n69: - **AND** `AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface` accessor SHALL be defined\n70: \n71: ### AR-035-008: CodeInterpreter typed client\n72: \n73: - **GIVEN** the CodeInterpreter typed client\n74: - **WHEN** defining CodeInterpreterInterface\n75: - **THEN** it SHALL have the same method shape as AgentRuntimeInterface\n76: - **AND** types SHALL be `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`\n77: - **AND** resource plural SHALL be `codeinterpreters`\n78: \n79: ### AR-035-009: Expansion hooks\n80: \n81: - **GIVEN** the generated expansion file\n82: - **WHEN** defining expansion interfaces\n83: - **THEN** there SHALL be empty `AgentRuntimeExpansion` interface\n84: - **AND** SHALL be empty `CodeInterpreterExpansion` interface\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## Scenario: Scheme Registration\n89: \n90: ### AR-035-010: Scheme builder\n91: \n92: - **GIVEN** the clientset versioned scheme package\n93: - **WHEN** creating register.go\n94: - **THEN** there SHALL be a `Scheme` builder function\n95: - **AND** SHALL be `Codecs` and `ParameterCodec` builders\n96: - **AND** SHALL provide `AddToScheme` to register runtime/v1alpha1 types\n97: \n98: ### AR-035-011: Package documentation\n99: \n100: - **GIVEN** the scheme package\n101: - **WHEN** creating doc.go\n102: - **THEN** it SHALL include package-level documentation\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## Scenario: Informer Factory Generation\n107: \n108: ### AR-035-012: SharedInformerFactory interface\n109: \n110: - **GIVEN** the informers package at `informers/externalversions`\n111: - **WHEN** generating informers\n112: - **THEN** there SHALL be `SharedInformerFactory` with Start, Shutdown, WaitForCacheSync, ForResource, InformerFor methods\n113: - **AND** SHALL have `Runtime() externalversionsruntime.Interface`\n114: \n115: ### AR-035-013: SharedInformerFactory constructors\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** SharedInformerFactory\n118: - **WHEN** creating constructors\n119: - **THEN** there SHALL be `NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)`\n120: - **AND** SHALL be `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options ...SharedInformerOption)`\n121: - **AND** Options SHALL include `WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n122: \n123: ### AR-035-014: Runtime group interface\n124: \n125: - **GIVEN** the runtime group informer package\n126: - **WHEN** defining the group interface\n127: - **THEN** there SHALL be `Interface` with `